3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The Max-logDet metric introduced in the paper is a machine learning technique used for feature selection. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper's focus on improving accuracy in pose tracking using feature selection is a common problem in AI applications. 
5. cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper's focus on feature selection for visual SLAM makes it relevant to the CVPR conference.
